As of today, Norway is added to countries enjoying China's 72/144 hr visa-free layover policy, which means Norwegian nationals passing through 23 Chinese cities may stay for 72/144 hrs without a visa.

legacy.description: @xhnews, Xinhua Institute, previously in Damascus/Washington. Usual disclaimers. Sign up for my newsletter @Beijingchannel, focusing on China's foreign affairs↓

legacy.full_text: The cities are Changsha, Harbin, Guilin (72hrs) and Beijing, Tianjin, Shijiazhuang, Qinhuangdao, Shanghai, Nanjing, Hangzhou, Ningbo, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Jieyang, Shenyang, Dalian, Qingdao, Chongqing, Chengdu, Xi'an, Wuhan and Kunming (144hrs)/2

legacy.full_text: A total of 54 countries now enjoy this policy. It's worth noting that the treatment is unilateral for many of the countries. Chinese authorities say more than half a million travelers have taken advantage of this policy since its launch in 2013. /End https://t.co/E3gUB61hm3
